  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "pVqQd4MfZP/Rf5YvEGXg8XTmctQ=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:32.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Each document on Swarm has a feed at topic `ph:v2:doc:<documentId>`. The feed points to a JSON manifest that indexes operation batches uploaded to `/bytes`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"documentId\": \"abc-123\",\n  \"documentType\": \"powerhouse/budget-statement\",\n  \"latestRevision\": { \"global\": 47 },\n  \"operationBatches\": [\n    { \"reference\": \"a1b2c3d4...\", \"scope\": \"global\", \"branch\": \"main\", \"startIndex\": 0,  \"endIndex\": 23, \"timestamp\": \"...\" },\n    { \"reference\": \"e5f6a7b8...\", \"scope\": \"global\", \"branch\": \"main\", \"startIndex\": 24, \"endIndex\": 47, \"timestamp\": \"...\" }\n  ],\n  \"encrypted\": true,\n  \"updatedAt\": \"2026-04-07T10:05:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nEach `reference` points to a `/bytes` upload containing the encrypted batch. `latestRevision` is keyed by scope, allowing multi-scope documents. `encrypted: true` signals the payload format; readers validate via the SWE prefix at `/bytes`.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:32.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:32.000Z"
    }
  },
